Hartbeespoort police arrested five suspects early on Thursday after a man was shot and killed during a hijacking in Broederstroom, Pretoria. According to information, the man and his wife, whose identities cannot be made public yet, stopped in their Nissan Tiida at the Lanseria T-junction in Broederstroom at about 7.20pm on Wednesday and were attacked by armed men driving a Toyota Quantum, Kormorant reported. The man was shot and killed, and the robbers fled with the couple s vehicle, said police spokesperson Warrant Officer Mpeile Talane. Police followed leads and worked through the night to track the suspected hijackers. Five men were arrested in Atteridgeville in Pretoria in the early hours this morning, and a number of firearms were recovered. Investigations are ongoing. &#8211; Caxton News Service